TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents the C-terminal region (approximately 38-68
CC   residues, positions 71-309) of HrgA, a protein found in type I
CC   restriction-modification systems. HrgA (Helicobacter pylori
CC   restriction endonuclease-replacing gene) replaces the restriction
CC   endonuclease in some type I R-M systems and has been associated with
CC   gastric cancer in Helicobacter pylori. The family is found in
CC   Pseudomonadota (Betaproteobacteria, Gammaproteobacteria) and
CC   Bacteroidota.
RN   [1]
RM   11956101
RT   A Helicobacter pylori restriction endonuclease-replacing gene, hrgA,
RT   is associated with gastric cancer in Asian strains.
RA   Higashi H, Tsutsumi R, Fujita A, Yamazaki S, Asaka M, Azuma T,
RA   Hatakeyama M;
RL   Cancer Res 2002;62:2385-2389.
